{%- comment -%}
  Swatch Colors
  --------------------------------
  In most cases the theme will convert color variant names into CSS colors that will work automatically.
  For example, the variant Color: "Light Blue" will be converted to a valid CSS color lightblue
  https://htmlcolorcodes.com/color-names/

  The swatches will convert your shop's color names to:
  - Lowercase
  - Remove any spaces

  Color: "Red and White" would become "redandwhite"
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Custom Color Names
  --------------------------------
  It is possible to add in custom color names or even overwrite the color HEX value of an existing CSS color.
  Use the following examples as a guide to create custom colors
    - Custom color name must begin with "swatch_color_"
    - Add the name of the product variant color all lowercase and without spaces
    - Adding an existing CSS color name to the end of "swatch_color_" overwrites the default CSS color
  
  The following examples are for:
    - Butter Yellow
    - Grape
    - Navy (overwriting the default #000080 value of the CSS color 'navy')
{%- endcomment -%}
